http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Bus-terminus-in-Yadgir-to-be-inaugurated-tomorrow/article13981824.ece

The much awaited new bus terminus in the city, which was constructed on four acres on the Hyderabad road at a cost of Rs 5.38 crore, will be opened from Wednesday.Transport Minister Ramalinga Reddy will inaugurate it. M. Mallikarjun Kharge, Leader of the Congress in the Lok Sabha; Baburao Chinchansur and Sharanaprakash Patil, Ministers; A.B. Maalakareddy, MLA, and Bhimanna Sali, chairman of the North Eastern Road Transport Corporation (NEKRTC), will be present. The bus terminus has 31 platforms and 12 shops and facilities such as canteen, rest rooms, computerised passengers information centre, and a parking area. The NEKRTC took up the project in 2012-13 under a special development plan and entrusted the work to three private contractors.